                          '<p>Primary CNS tumors account for about 15–20% of pediatric malignancies. They are the '
                          'second most common pediatric malignancy after hematologic cancers, the most common '
                          'pediatric solid organ tumor, and the leading cause of cancer death in children age 0–14. '
