                          '      <tr><td>Ependymoma</td><td>54–59.4 Gy to tumor bed; 36 Gy CSI only for metastatic '
                          'disease and age &gt;3</td><td>Mainly used to convert subtotal resection to resectable '
                          'disease</td></tr>\n'
                          '      <tr><td>Low-grade glioma</td><td>Observation until progression, even after subtotal '
                          'resection</td><td>Targeted therapies increasingly important</td></tr>\n'
                          '      <tr><td>High-grade glioma</td><td>54 Gy after gross total resection; 59.4 Gy after '
                          'subtotal resection</td><td>Chemotherapy benefit limited; clinical trial '
                          'preferred</td></tr>\n'
                          '      <tr><td>Craniopharyngioma</td><td>Observe after gross total resection; otherwise 54 '
                          'Gy/30 fractions or selected SRS</td><td>Not applicable</td></tr>\n'
                          '      <tr><td>Germinoma</td><td>Whole-ventricle irradiation plus primary boost; after '
                          'chemotherapy, 18 Gy WVI if CR or 24 Gy if PR plus 12 Gy '
